<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id77064fc3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s115a"><num value="115a">§ 115a.</num><heading> Mineral resources; exploitation</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">After <date date="1931-01-26">January 26, 1931</date>, no permit, license, lease, or other authorization for the prospecting, development, or utilization of the mineral resources within the Mesa Verde National Park, Colorado, shall be granted or made.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id77064fc4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1931-01-26/ch47/s1">Jan. 26, 1931, ch. 47, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/46/1043">46 Stat. 1043</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
